I personally use this with the terminal version of Vim on OS X Lion. I had to recompile Vim to enable ruby support using the guide here:

http://brilliantcorners.org/2011/02/building-vim-on-osx-snow-leopard/#comment-299516619

Installation:

    git clone git://github.com/TimFletcher/dotvim.git ~/.vim

Create symlinks:

    ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc

Switch to the `~/.vim` directory, and fetch submodules:

    cd ~/.vim
    git submodule init
    git submodule update
